        "headerTitle": "How Insurance Costs Work Together",
        "layout": "generic",
        "layoutData": {
          "paragraphs": [
            "Regular monthly payment keeps your coverage activeâ€”you pay this whether you use insurance or not",
            "When you receive care, you pay the full cost until you've paid your annual deductible amount",
            "After meeting your deductible, you pay your percentage (e.g., 20%) of additional costs",
            "You keep paying your percentage until you reach your annual out-of-pocket maximum",
            "Once you hit your out-of-pocket max, insurance covers 100% of covered services for the rest of the year"
          ],
